main event: Observation of a bright flashing light in the sky, possibly a satellite, on 23 Aug 63.
interesting points: The object was observed moving at a fast speed of 130 degrees per second., The observation was made using ground-radar., The object appeared as bright as a second magnitude star., The weather conditions were described as calm sea with scattered clouds., ECHO data for verification was unavailable, leaving the identification uncertain.
witness description: Data insufficient for a witness account.
